<br>
You're wasting a slot that could be used on stats for a bow.  If you aren't pulling, that bow shouldn't be there, period.  I have an idol and a bow, I use em when they are appropriate.<br>
<br>
If you want aggro for a reasonable price, you use a frostbringer.  Venom axe sucks.  Bloodpoint sucks, defiance sucks.  There is no weapon under 10k that will put out the damage and the taunt that a frostbringer will, and the old phrase &quot;beggars can't be choosers&quot; comes to mind.  When you have something better than a frostbringer for damage and aggro, then you can afford to be choosy.  Until then, bite the bullet and get one, or nothing else you get is going to matter at all, because you won't be taking any hits because the mob isn't going to look twice at you.<br>
<br>
There's plenty of room for individuality for warriors, however weapons unfortunately aren't one of them.  You use what you have to in order to keep the mob on you, and off the robes. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Veteran Haass Wolvesbane</a> <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Venerable Cagna Soulshaker</a> 

